7 mm hysteroscope in a medium of 0.

9% saline, and the image was transmitted to a screen visible to the patient.

 A Visual Scale Analogue (VAS) consisting of a 10 cm line was used to assess the intensity of pain experienced during and after the procedure.

 Overall patient satisfaction was assessed during, immediately after, 15 minutes later, and three days post hysteroscopy.

