This randomized clinical trial compares two methods of diagnostic hysteroscopy: vaginoscopic hysteroscopy vs.

 traditional method.

 Pain intensity was estimated using a visual analogue scale (VAS), and patient satisfaction was evaluated.

 These endpoints were compared by treatment assignment.

 Vaginoscopic hysteroscopy was associated with significantly lower VAS scores, indicating reduced experience of pain in this treatment group; however, this was not associated with improved patient satisfaction.

